		<td width="10%" nowrap="nowrap">Post subject:&nbsp;</td>
		<td><b></b></td>
	</tr>
	<tr>
		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" />I bought a toploader and have not been happy with it.  The RF only is a pain for me, but it sounds like it's not an issue for you.  The <span class="posthilit">vertical</span> lines are extremely noticeable, and hence I never play games on the toploader.  However, I do quite a bit of hardware hacking and the toploader is good for that because:
<br />1. It does not have a lockout chip on it, meaning neither do my games.
<br />2. You can put a EEPROM'd cart into it without having to tear the thing apart.  (actually I use a somewhat rare "game genie extender" for this).

		

		</td>
	</tr>
	</table>


	<hr width="85%" />

	<table width="85%" cellspacing="3" cellpadding="0" border="0" align="center">
