	<tr>
		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" />It would be interesting to have a bunch of PCBs and plastic top-loader style cases made, so that we could harvest toasters and player's choice 10 boards for chips.  But making plastic parts is expensive in small quantities and tearing apart classic console hardware is somewhat of a bad thing, IMO.  It is better to just refurbish toasters, and mod RF famicoms and USA top loaders to have AV.
<br />
<br />Modding a NES to have RGB is allot harder than you'd think, even with the right chip:
<br /><!-- m --><a class="postlink" href="http://nfg.2y.net/forum/index.php?showtopic=187">http://nfg.2y.net/forum/index.php?showtopic=187</a><!-- m -->

		

